Configure JAAS. The JAAS configuration assists the Java Virtual Machine (JVM) in using the appropriate LoginModule to handle authentication. Configuring JAAS is done through the use of config files. 
      Example contents of a JAAS config file:
      /** Login config for JAAS **/
      AppLoginConfig {      application.auth.LoginMod required;};
      Once the config files are set, they can be loaded by using the -Djava.security.auth.login.config flag when loading the JVM instance that will host the application.

Utilize the LoginContext.
        LoginContext provides the mechanism for invoking the appropriate LoginModule in JAAS. Once the JAAS configuration is loaded, the application must specify which configuration is to be used by JAAS. After LoginContext is utilized, use the login() function to invoke the JAAS authentication procedure. Example:
      LoginContext auth = new LoginContext("AppLoginConfig", new CallbackHandler()); ... auth.login();

